# OpenHand CODEOWNERS
#
# Anyone listed here is auto-requested for review on PRs touching their
# subtree. The repo owner is the catch-all so a PR never sits unrouted.
# Keep this list short — every entry costs maintainer attention.
#
# Syntax: <pattern> <handle> [more handles...]
# Patterns are gitignore-style; the LAST matching line wins.

# Catch-all — owner of the repo.
*                                @Ricardo-M-L

# Core runtime
/packages/core/                  @Ricardo-M-L
/packages/llm/                   @Ricardo-M-L
/packages/sandbox/               @Ricardo-M-L
/packages/tools/                 @Ricardo-M-L

# Apps
/apps/cli/                       @Ricardo-M-L
/apps/server/                    @Ricardo-M-L
/apps/web/                       @Ricardo-M-L

# Plugins (community contributions land here — extra-friendly review).
/plugins/                        @Ricardo-M-L

# Build / release / CI surface — sensitive, owner-only.
/.github/                        @Ricardo-M-L
/scripts/                        @Ricardo-M-L
/Dockerfile.server               @Ricardo-M-L
/docker-compose.yml              @Ricardo-M-L

# Docs are explicitly first-PR-friendly: owner reviews, no extra gating.
/docs/                           @Ricardo-M-L
/cookbook/                       @Ricardo-M-L
/README.md                       @Ricardo-M-L
